1
00:00:38,271 --> 00:00:41,172
I like this for the powder room,
but definitely not the bedroom.

2
00:00:41,274 --> 00:00:42,332
It's a little busy.

3
00:00:42,442 --> 00:00:43,773
I'm not sure.

4
00:00:43,876 --> 00:00:46,344
It's not the curtains
I'm worried about, but the cabinets.

5
00:00:46,446 --> 00:00:49,006
Nixon didn't stand a chance.

6
00:00:49,115 --> 00:00:53,347
The Browns trounced
the Redskins, 31-10.

7
00:00:53,453 --> 00:00:55,080
The result of that last home game

8
00:00:55,188 --> 00:00:58,646
has correctly predicted
the last six elections.

9
00:00:58,758 --> 00:01:01,625
I wish someone would have told me that.

10
00:01:01,728 --> 00:01:05,687
Of course, it's really
a 50/50 chance of being right.

11
00:01:09,769 --> 00:01:15,469
I want to treat you like a son because...
I feel that way towards you.

12
00:01:15,575 --> 00:01:17,668
Okay.

13
00:01:17,777 --> 00:01:21,042
Trudy told us that you
were up for a promotion

14
00:01:21,147 --> 00:01:23,172
and you didn't get it or something.

15
00:01:23,283 --> 00:01:24,750
I wish she hadn't.

16
00:01:24,851 --> 00:01:27,513
Now, she loves you.

17
00:01:27,620 --> 00:01:29,110
And honestly,

18
00:01:29,222 --> 00:01:32,089
I think you need
to take a little focus off your work.

19
00:01:32,191 --> 00:01:35,354
This from one of the top
salesmen at Vicks Chemical.

20
00:01:35,461 --> 00:01:36,758
When you started talking

21
00:01:36,863 --> 00:01:38,990
about that Clearasil
company you bought...

22
00:01:39,098 --> 00:01:40,759
Now, that was kind of
worth bragging about.

23
00:01:40,867 --> 00:01:43,335
Did you know that there's a surge
in adolescence right now?

24
00:01:43,436 --> 00:01:47,463
I'll tell you, Sterling Cooper
and yours truly

25
00:01:47,573 --> 00:01:50,098
would love to help you
deliver that message.

26
00:01:50,209 --> 00:01:52,336
See? Now that's what I'm talking about.

27
00:01:52,445 --> 00:01:54,242
The only family and business
you should be mixing

28
00:01:54,347 --> 00:01:56,815
is the production of a child.

29
00:01:56,916 --> 00:01:59,009
And what did Trudy say about that?

30
00:01:59,118 --> 00:02:00,142
About what?

31
00:02:00,253 --> 00:02:03,984
Tom, loose lips sink ships.

32
00:02:04,090 --> 00:02:06,024
I was just saying that work
isn't everything, you know.

33
00:02:06,125 --> 00:02:09,583
It's like that song says:
Um, tend your own garden.

34
00:02:09,696 --> 00:02:11,357
What song is that, Daddy?

35
00:02:11,464 --> 00:02:12,396
Uh, I don't know.

36
00:02:12,498 --> 00:02:13,465
People say it. It's true.

37
00:02:13,566 --> 00:02:14,533
It is true.

38
00:02:14,634 --> 00:02:15,862
Yeah. Tend to your own garden.

39
00:02:15,968 --> 00:02:20,132
That means... you know,
start growing things.

40
00:02:20,239 --> 00:02:21,604
Daddy!

41
00:02:21,708 --> 00:02:22,936
You're embarrassing us.

42
00:02:23,042 --> 00:02:25,272
It'll be the best Christmas present
this one ever had.

43
00:02:25,378 --> 00:02:27,107
And hell, Thanksgiving's Thursday.

44
00:02:33,386 --> 00:02:38,050
Oh, and I guess I should go to Keppler Farm
to get some acorn squash.

45
00:02:38,157 --> 00:02:40,455
What am I doing?
They have squash there.

46
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:42,460
Ery good squash, actually.

47
00:02:46,265 --> 00:02:48,631
I wish you would come.

48
00:02:48,735 --> 00:02:51,363
Birdie, I'm a partner.

49
00:02:51,471 --> 00:02:54,065
80% of my business
rolls out next week.

50
00:02:54,173 --> 00:02:55,265
It just seems silly for me

51
00:02:55,375 --> 00:02:58,503
to go down there
for a 12-hour Thanksgiving.

52
00:02:58,611 --> 00:03:03,776
What about... Sally and Bobby's
childhood memories?

53
00:03:05,651 --> 00:03:08,643
There was no reason
you couldn't have it up here.

54
00:03:08,755 --> 00:03:10,655
You know my brother's
children are animals.

55
00:03:10,757 --> 00:03:12,054
They can't make the trip up here,

56
00:03:12,158 --> 00:03:14,683
and I don't want my dad to be alone.

57
00:03:15,395 --> 00:03:20,833
I'll take a cab to the train,
and William will pick us up,

58
00:03:20,933 --> 00:03:23,163
probably in some new car.

59
00:03:28,508 --> 00:03:29,975
You know what? L...

60
00:03:31,411 --> 00:03:33,504
I don't think you want to go.

61
00:03:35,314 --> 00:03:37,475
I'm sorry. Was I unclear about that?

62
00:03:43,256 --> 00:03:44,587
I don't understand

63
00:03:44,690 --> 00:03:47,284
why you can't make
my family your family.

64
00:03:55,968 --> 00:03:58,493
Ken is perfectly happy to have me here.

65
00:04:00,807 --> 00:04:04,903
What do you think it's like?
He's a bachelor. It's dirty.

66
00:04:05,011 --> 00:04:06,842
I'm not complaining.

67
00:04:09,449 --> 00:04:12,680
I don't think it's a good idea
to spend money on a hotel right now.

68
00:04:12,785 --> 00:04:15,754
If you're so worried about my well-being,
let me come home.

69
00:04:18,691 --> 00:04:20,249
That's not what I meant.

70
00:04:22,628 --> 00:04:25,290
I mean, I know how it sounded.

71
00:04:28,835 --> 00:04:30,393
Jennifer.

72
00:04:42,048 --> 00:04:43,208
Yes.

73
00:04:43,316 --> 00:04:46,080
I'll quit if you let me come home.

74
00:04:50,556 --> 00:04:52,148
I miss you...

75
00:04:53,326 --> 00:04:55,123
so much.

76
00:05:08,508 --> 00:05:11,409
Those the legendary
secret files of Bert Cooper?

77
00:05:11,511 --> 00:05:12,637
No.

78
00:05:12,745 --> 00:05:15,805
I got a call from Abraham Menken.

79
00:05:15,915 --> 00:05:17,906
I'm sure you know
that his daughter will be unavailable

80
00:05:18,017 --> 00:05:19,348
for the next three months,

81
00:05:19,452 --> 00:05:24,583
taking some sort of ocean voyage
to Paris and whatnot.

82
00:05:24,690 --> 00:05:26,487
I hadn't heard that.

83
00:05:29,228 --> 00:05:30,456
But otherwise?

84
00:05:30,563 --> 00:05:32,588
There is no otherwise.

85
00:05:32,698 --> 00:05:37,135
Why is this man calling me?

86
00:05:37,236 --> 00:05:40,137
I don't know. Is he unhappy?

87
00:05:40,239 --> 00:05:43,538
As a partner, I do not expect
your personal preferences

88
00:05:43,643 --> 00:05:45,611
to interfere with our business.

89
00:05:45,711 --> 00:05:47,508
Who says they have?

90
00:05:47,613 --> 00:05:49,240
It was the tone of his voice.

91
00:05:49,348 --> 00:05:50,645
He's her father.

92
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:52,274
That's it, cowboy.

93
00:06:01,661 --> 00:06:02,593
Francine.

94
00:06:02,695 --> 00:06:05,664
I'm coming in. I'm freezing.

95
00:06:07,967 --> 00:06:09,559
You're in your slippers.

96
00:06:09,669 --> 00:06:11,398
I've been outside
waiting for you to come home,

97
00:06:11,504 --> 00:06:14,268
just sitting in the car
hoping no one would see me.

98
00:06:14,373 --> 00:06:15,806
What's going on?

99
00:06:15,908 --> 00:06:17,239
Are your kids home?

100
00:06:17,343 --> 00:06:19,607
No. What happened?

101
00:06:20,947 --> 00:06:22,642
I'm so stupid.

102
00:06:23,816 --> 00:06:25,681
So damn stupid.

103
00:06:26,819 --> 00:06:29,686
You're not, Francine.

104
00:06:29,789 --> 00:06:32,758
Whatever happened, you're not stupid.

105
00:06:32,858 --> 00:06:36,453
My mind hasn't been so sharp
since I had the baby.

106
00:06:36,562 --> 00:06:38,052
And Carlton gave me a stack of mail,

107
00:06:38,164 --> 00:06:40,655
and honestly I think I just threw it away.

108
00:06:40,766 --> 00:06:42,461
And four days later,
the phone was cut off,

109
00:06:42,568 --> 00:06:47,437
so I had to go to the phone company
and pay it, or, you know, he'd have a fit.

110
00:06:47,540 --> 00:06:50,236
And I had to do all this
without him knowing.

111
00:06:50,343 --> 00:06:51,833
How perfect.

112
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:57,408
I don't understand.

113
00:06:57,516 --> 00:06:58,949
They gave me the bill.

114
00:07:01,954 --> 00:07:05,446
It was close to $18.

115
00:07:05,558 --> 00:07:07,526
There were all these calls:

116
00:07:07,627 --> 00:07:10,528
Long distance, MH.

117
00:07:10,630 --> 00:07:13,030
MH? Manhattan?

118
00:07:16,035 --> 00:07:17,662
So I called one.

119
00:07:19,538 --> 00:07:22,405
A woman answered.

120
00:07:22,508 --> 00:07:24,806
I had just...

121
00:07:24,910 --> 00:07:28,710
I said, "I'm calling
from Carlton Hanson's office. "

122
00:07:28,814 --> 00:07:30,475
She said, "Really?"

123
00:07:30,583 --> 00:07:34,644
I said, "He wants to have dinner
tonight at the usual place. "

124
00:07:34,754 --> 00:07:36,585
What made you say that?

125
00:07:42,395 --> 00:07:46,923
What woman would he
be calling in Manhattan

126
00:07:47,033 --> 00:07:49,524
who answers her own phone?

127
00:07:51,504 --> 00:07:53,062
Married women.

128
00:07:53,172 --> 00:07:56,573
Lots of women answer
their own phones.

129
00:07:56,676 --> 00:07:59,873
So he's calling some married woman
from my house

130
00:07:59,979 --> 00:08:03,107
while I'm upstairs sleeping?

131
00:08:03,215 --> 00:08:05,513
Maybe it's a caterer.

132
00:08:05,618 --> 00:08:08,280
Maybe he's throwing you
a surprise party.

133
00:08:13,693 --> 00:08:18,392
Do you know he spends
two nights a week at the Waldorf?

134
00:08:18,497 --> 00:08:21,489
I'm so stupid.

135
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:23,363
Assuming the worst...

136
00:08:25,271 --> 00:08:28,240
The worst is that I'll poison him.

137
00:08:28,340 --> 00:08:31,104
He's so stupid, he'd drink anything.

138
00:08:34,113 --> 00:08:37,344
I'm going to have
a house full of people.

139
00:08:37,450 --> 00:08:39,077
I'll poison them all:

140
00:08:39,185 --> 00:08:43,645
His parents, my parents...

141
00:08:43,756 --> 00:08:44,916
my kids.

142
00:08:45,024 --> 00:08:46,423
Stop it.

143
00:08:46,525 --> 00:08:48,789
Stop that, Francine.

144
00:08:50,196 --> 00:08:52,460
You're emotional. It doesn't mean...

145
00:08:52,565 --> 00:08:55,762
Damn it, Betty. I know everything.

146
00:08:55,868 --> 00:08:57,597
What am I going to do?

147
00:08:57,703 --> 00:08:59,898
I've been sitting outside in the car.

148
00:09:00,005 --> 00:09:02,565
What do I do? I thought
you'd know what to do.

149
00:09:04,376 --> 00:09:07,209
Me? L... Why?

150
00:09:10,549 --> 00:09:12,574
I don't know.

151
00:09:22,361 --> 00:09:24,124
I'm s...

152
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:26,528
so embarrassed.

153
00:09:29,535 --> 00:09:31,560
He doesn't know you know.

154
00:09:31,670 --> 00:09:33,001
I know that.

155
00:09:35,975 --> 00:09:36,964
Go on upstairs.

156
00:09:37,076 --> 00:09:38,475
I should go.

157
00:09:38,577 --> 00:09:41,011
Come on, Bobby,
let's go play in my room.

158
00:09:41,113 --> 00:09:43,138
No. Don't.

159
00:09:43,249 --> 00:09:45,274
It'll be okay.

160
00:09:45,384 --> 00:09:48,080
Mrs. Draper, sorry I'm late.

161
00:09:48,187 --> 00:09:51,179
Oh. It's okay, Carla. You can go.

162
00:09:51,290 --> 00:09:52,757
You want me to unpack the groceries?

163
00:09:52,858 --> 00:09:55,156
I'll do it. Just go.

164
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:57,058
Good-bye.

165
00:10:47,479 --> 00:10:48,673
First things first.

166
00:10:48,781 --> 00:10:50,146
When I call a meeting,

167
00:10:50,249 --> 00:10:52,774
if you arrive after me, you are late.

168
00:10:54,153 --> 00:10:56,212
Boys, the stock in our stable:

169
00:10:56,322 --> 00:10:59,814
Lucky Strike, Bethlehem Steel, Maytag.

170
00:10:59,925 --> 00:11:03,383
No automobile, airline,
pharmaceuticals.

171
00:11:03,495 --> 00:11:06,089
Tobacco is on that list.

172
00:11:06,198 --> 00:11:07,756
You're Cosgrove, right?

173
00:11:07,867 --> 00:11:11,769
The powerhouse
behind the Rejuvenator?

174
00:11:11,871 --> 00:11:15,398
Actually, it's called
the Relax-a-Cizor now.

175
00:11:15,507 --> 00:11:16,838
What the hell is it?

176
00:11:16,942 --> 00:11:20,537
It's a weight loss device
with a female pleasure payload.

177
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:22,806
Really?

178
00:11:24,083 --> 00:11:25,675
I'm offering a hundred-dollar bonus

179
00:11:25,784 --> 00:11:29,743
to the first man who brings me
a meeting with a decision maker.

180
00:11:29,855 --> 00:11:33,655
Gentlemen, here's a list of people
you should be having lunch with.

181
00:11:33,759 --> 00:11:36,785
I want you to run into people,
go through old yearbooks.

182
00:11:36,896 --> 00:11:39,865
This means everybody. Writers, too.

183
00:11:39,965 --> 00:11:41,364
Bringing in business is the key

184
00:11:41,467 --> 00:11:44,129
to your salary, your status,
and your self-worth.

185
00:11:44,236 --> 00:11:45,828
I went to the Athletic Club today,

186
00:11:45,938 --> 00:11:48,736
and I sat in the steam
for an hour and a half.

187
00:11:48,841 --> 00:11:50,399
In that time, I lost 4 pounds

188
00:11:50,509 --> 00:11:52,238
and learned that Kodak still isn't happy

189
00:11:52,344 --> 00:11:54,244
with the campaign
for the new slide projector.

190
00:11:54,346 --> 00:11:56,610
Is any of this sinking in?

191
00:12:00,719 --> 00:12:03,745
"It's true that while simply relaxing,

192
00:12:03,856 --> 00:12:06,620
"I can get all the benefits
of calisthenics.

193
00:12:06,725 --> 00:12:10,126
"A simple regimen of three
20-minute sessions per week,

194
00:12:10,229 --> 00:12:12,026
"combined with a sensible diet,

195
00:12:12,131 --> 00:12:14,258
"will restore your youthful glow.

196
00:12:14,366 --> 00:12:17,130
"I love the way it makes me feel.

197
00:12:17,236 --> 00:12:18,669
"The Relax-a-Cizor.

198
00:12:18,771 --> 00:12:20,864
It's my little secret. "

199
00:12:22,374 --> 00:12:24,604
Thank you, Annie.

200
00:12:24,710 --> 00:12:28,373
Uh, one more time... Rita.

201
00:12:29,648 --> 00:12:31,616
"I never thought it would happen to me,

202
00:12:31,717 --> 00:12:34,584
"but I regained my youth
and my happiness.

203
00:12:34,687 --> 00:12:36,450
- Just ask my husband. "
- Todd?

204
00:12:36,555 --> 00:12:38,580
I think we're both going
to agree on Annie.

205
00:12:38,691 --> 00:12:40,022
Which one is Annie?

206
00:12:41,593 --> 00:12:43,686
Believe it or not, I like Rita.

207
00:12:43,796 --> 00:12:47,425
She's got that voice:
Randy and knowing,

208
00:12:47,533 --> 00:12:48,932
like the Relax-a-Cizor.

209
00:12:49,034 --> 00:12:52,526
Annie belongs on TV
with Rita's voice dubbed in.

210
00:12:55,207 --> 00:12:56,231
Norma, thank you.

211
00:12:56,342 --> 00:12:57,366
You can go.

212
00:12:59,778 --> 00:13:01,040
Whatever the...

213
00:13:01,146 --> 00:13:04,513
special properties
of the Relax-a-Cizor are,

214
00:13:04,616 --> 00:13:08,950
what we are selling is confidence,
a better you.

215
00:13:09,054 --> 00:13:10,715
That woman isn't a better anything.

216
00:13:10,823 --> 00:13:16,284
Annie is a confident, beautiful woman,
and you can hear it in her voice.

217
00:13:16,395 --> 00:13:18,863
I can't believe I'm in this argument.

218
00:13:18,964 --> 00:13:20,693
Sorry about that, Rita.

219
00:13:20,799 --> 00:13:22,790
Hi, Annie. We'll do this tomorrow.

220
00:13:22,901 --> 00:13:24,300
Check with Peggy here
for your session.

221
00:13:27,172 --> 00:13:28,730
If I get a hard time about this,

222
00:13:28,841 --> 00:13:30,240
I'm telling people it was your idea.

223
00:13:30,342 --> 00:13:32,207
It was my idea.

224
00:13:46,258 --> 00:13:49,318
Just a minute. I'll be right back.

225
00:13:52,798 --> 00:13:55,198
Do you have to?

226
00:13:55,300 --> 00:13:57,928
Peter.

227
00:13:58,037 --> 00:14:01,438
That's risky business.

228
00:14:01,540 --> 00:14:03,701
It is, isn't it?

229
00:14:07,713 --> 00:14:10,375
What, honey?

230
00:14:10,482 --> 00:14:12,609
You can say anything to me.

231
00:14:19,758 --> 00:14:25,196
I can't provide for a child
on what I make.

232
00:14:26,765 --> 00:14:28,630
Don't worry about that.

233
00:14:32,237 --> 00:14:34,671
How could I not?

234
00:14:34,773 --> 00:14:36,502
You can't.

235
00:14:37,976 --> 00:14:40,069
Really?

236
00:14:40,179 --> 00:14:42,773
You can't worry about that.

237
00:14:52,658 --> 00:14:54,592
So stay here.

238
00:15:04,603 --> 00:15:07,936
Oh... Peter.

239
00:15:22,788 --> 00:15:23,755
Hi, Birdie.

240
00:15:28,827 --> 00:15:31,660
It's 9:30. Why didn't you
just stay in the city?

241
00:15:31,763 --> 00:15:35,290
Oh, I have work to do here as well.

242
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:38,665
Do you know where
the slide projector is?

243
00:15:38,770 --> 00:15:41,034
So you're not going
to see us for four days,

244
00:15:41,140 --> 00:15:42,903
and you're not going to see us now.

245
00:15:43,008 --> 00:15:44,737
Bets, right when I walk in the door?

246
00:15:48,313 --> 00:15:49,610
I'm sorry.

247
00:15:51,316 --> 00:15:54,342
I'm sorry. I just... I had a terrible day.

248
00:15:57,456 --> 00:15:59,617
Sit with me.

249
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:09,458
What happened?

250
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:14,765
Francine told me

251
00:16:14,873 --> 00:16:16,704
Carlton has been having an affair.

252
00:16:18,644 --> 00:16:20,771
Really?

253
00:16:22,347 --> 00:16:23,905
She was in pieces, Don.

254
00:16:24,016 --> 00:16:25,210
I didn't know what to say to her.

255
00:16:25,317 --> 00:16:28,252
Well, what could you say?

256
00:16:28,353 --> 00:16:29,911
I'm surprised she told you.

257
00:16:30,022 --> 00:16:31,785
Why?

258
00:16:31,890 --> 00:16:34,017
She's like a sister to me.

259
00:16:34,126 --> 00:16:36,287
Of course she is.

260
00:16:41,633 --> 00:16:43,794
I never liked Carlton.

261
00:16:43,902 --> 00:16:46,962
He was never my favorite.

262
00:16:47,072 --> 00:16:49,472
She should poison him.

263
00:16:49,575 --> 00:16:52,203
Now you think she should kill him?

264
00:16:52,311 --> 00:16:56,213
