because wheels aren't really seen
as exciting technology,

534
00:38:30,841 --> 00:38:32,240
even though they are the original.

535
00:38:32,343 --> 00:38:38,213
Well, technology is a glittering lure,

536
00:38:38,315 --> 00:38:40,510
but there's the rare occasion

537
00:38:40,618 --> 00:38:44,019
when the public can be engaged
on the level beyond flash,

538
00:38:44,121 --> 00:38:48,956
if they have a sentimental
bond with the product.

539
00:38:49,059 --> 00:38:53,291
My first job,
I was in house at a fur company

540
00:38:53,397 --> 00:38:57,128
with this old pro copyrighter,
a Greek named Teddy.

541
00:38:57,234 --> 00:39:03,173
And Teddy told me the most
important idea in advertising is "new. "

542
00:39:04,275 --> 00:39:05,936
Creates an itch.

543
00:39:06,043 --> 00:39:07,738
You simply put your product in there

544
00:39:07,845 --> 00:39:10,279
as a kind of... calamine lotion.

545
00:39:11,515 --> 00:39:16,714
He also talked about a deeper bond
with the product.

546
00:39:16,820 --> 00:39:19,152
Nostalgia.

547
00:39:19,256 --> 00:39:22,419
It's delicate...

548
00:39:22,526 --> 00:39:24,653
but potent.

549
00:39:24,762 --> 00:39:26,127
Sweetheart.

550
00:39:36,840 --> 00:39:39,206
Teddy told me that in Greek,

551
00:39:39,310 --> 00:39:44,805
nostalgia literally means
the pain from an old wound.

552
00:39:49,353 --> 00:39:51,981
It's a twinge in your heart

553
00:39:52,089 --> 00:39:55,490
far more powerful than memory alone.

554
00:39:57,962 --> 00:39:59,759
This device...

555
00:39:59,863 --> 00:40:02,889
isn't a space ship.

556
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:05,264
It's a time machine.

557
00:40:08,906 --> 00:40:12,273
It goes backwards, forwards.

558
00:40:17,314 --> 00:40:22,616
It takes us to a place
where we ache to go again.

559
00:40:28,726 --> 00:40:30,557
It's not called the Wheel.

560
00:40:32,129 --> 00:40:34,359
It's called the Carousel.

561
00:40:38,836 --> 00:40:43,136
It lets us travel the way a child travels.

562
00:40:44,675 --> 00:40:48,338
Around and around
and back home again...

563
00:40:52,750 --> 00:40:55,981
to a place where we know
we are loved.

564
00:41:31,188 --> 00:41:33,383
Good luck at your next meeting.

565
00:41:38,195 --> 00:41:40,390
Don, I have to warn you, I'm not alone.

566
00:41:40,497 --> 00:41:41,930
It was beautiful.

567
00:41:42,032 --> 00:41:44,557
<i>Congratulations, mein Kommandant.</i>

568
00:41:44,668 --> 00:41:45,965
They called from the lobby.

569
00:41:46,070 --> 00:41:48,800
They cancelled their other meetings,
including DDB.

570
00:41:48,906 --> 00:41:50,237
Not just a victory for us.

571
00:41:50,340 --> 00:41:51,466
It's a victory for civilization.

572
00:41:51,575 --> 00:41:53,873
There's also more celebrating.

573
00:41:53,977 --> 00:41:56,878
Mr. Campbell, here,
your father-in-law called.

574
00:41:56,980 --> 00:41:58,811
He'll be in before Christmas.

575
00:41:58,916 --> 00:42:00,747
I've got to get married.

576
00:42:02,052 --> 00:42:04,247
No, thank you. I'm good.

577
00:42:09,526 --> 00:42:10,424
Here's how.

578
00:42:10,527 --> 00:42:11,585
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

579
00:42:14,732 --> 00:42:16,996
You know what, Pete?

580
00:42:17,101 --> 00:42:20,730
I've got a way for you
to turn this account into a home run.

581
00:42:20,838 --> 00:42:23,170
He's on a roll.

582
00:42:23,273 --> 00:42:24,638
Clearasil.

583
00:42:24,742 --> 00:42:26,767
You know who buys that?

584
00:42:26,877 --> 00:42:28,606
Young girls.

585
00:42:28,712 --> 00:42:31,840
What a difference it makes in their lives
to be blemish-free.

586
00:42:31,949 --> 00:42:33,746
I believe it does.

587
00:42:33,851 --> 00:42:37,218
We have the perfect writer for that.

588
00:42:37,321 --> 00:42:38,788
Peggy Olsen.

589
00:42:40,224 --> 00:42:41,885
That's funny.

590
00:42:41,992 --> 00:42:45,428
Freddy Rumsen and I were both
very impressed with her insight.

591
00:42:45,529 --> 00:42:46,393
Freddy Rumsen.

592
00:42:46,497 --> 00:42:47,828
- If I can weigh in...
- No.

593
00:42:47,931 --> 00:42:49,398
Come on. That Belle Jolie thing.

594
00:42:49,500 --> 00:42:51,525
Plus you should have seen her
in that booth yesterday.

595
00:42:51,635 --> 00:42:53,227
She was like Kinsey but with balls.

596
00:42:54,404 --> 00:42:55,928
Stop joking already, will you, Don?

597
00:42:56,039 --> 00:42:57,336
Excuse me?

598
00:42:57,441 --> 00:42:59,932
This is my father-in-law.

599
00:43:00,043 --> 00:43:01,738
He's expecting the very best.

600
00:43:01,845 --> 00:43:04,245
I'm expecting the very best,

601
00:43:04,348 --> 00:43:07,977
not some little girl who'll walk away.

602
00:43:08,085 --> 00:43:11,384
You'll have to give back
that copy of Ayn Rand.

603
00:43:11,488 --> 00:43:13,513
Do you know how hard I worked
to get this account?

604
00:43:13,624 --> 00:43:14,716
Who the hell is she?

605
00:43:14,825 --> 00:43:16,656
Peggy is not even a copywriter.

606
00:43:16,760 --> 00:43:17,818
She's a... a secretary.

607
00:43:17,928 --> 00:43:18,895
Peggy!

608
00:43:18,996 --> 00:43:20,657
Yes, Mr. Draper?

609
00:43:20,764 --> 00:43:24,825
Miss Olsen, you are now a junior copywriter.

610
00:43:24,935 --> 00:43:29,497
Your first account will be delivering
Clearasil to the spotted masses.

611
00:43:29,606 --> 00:43:30,732
What?

612
00:43:30,841 --> 00:43:32,502
Don't act surprised.

613
00:43:32,609 --> 00:43:35,009
Is this really happening?

614
00:43:36,880 --> 00:43:38,040
Yes, it is.

615
00:43:39,550 --> 00:43:40,847
My goodness.

616
00:43:43,086 --> 00:43:46,021
I will do my sincere best.

617
00:43:48,225 --> 00:43:49,852
Good to hear.

618
00:43:49,960 --> 00:43:53,691
Mr. Campbell, here,
will brief you after the holiday.

619
00:43:57,301 --> 00:43:59,963
Of course.

620
00:44:00,070 --> 00:44:01,662
That'll be all.

621
00:44:01,772 --> 00:44:04,536
Thank you, Mr. Draper.

622
00:44:09,112 --> 00:44:12,047
I said congratulations, didn't I?

623
00:44:12,149 --> 00:44:14,845
Although sometimes when
people get what they want,

624
00:44:14,952 --> 00:44:17,147
they realize how limited
their goals were.

625
00:44:17,254 --> 00:44:19,552
So I guess I'll put you
in with Victor Manning.

626
00:44:19,656 --> 00:44:21,556
David Steuben got fired.

627
00:44:21,658 --> 00:44:22,920
Fired?

628
00:44:23,026 --> 00:44:24,493
People hated his work.

629
00:44:25,762 --> 00:44:27,093
Will I get business cards?

630
00:44:28,932 --> 00:44:31,457
Please make all your
requests through Bridget.

631
00:44:31,568 --> 00:44:32,500
Of course.

632
00:44:32,603 --> 00:44:34,161
Peggy, I know you a little.

633
00:44:34,271 --> 00:44:36,865
Remember, just because
you now have a door,

634
00:44:36,974 --> 00:44:39,169
don't forget that once you didn't.

635
00:44:39,276 --> 00:44:42,040
Think of the other girls,
or they won't think of you.

636
00:44:44,414 --> 00:44:46,905
Vic Manning, I'd like you
to meet Peggy Olsen.

637
00:44:47,017 --> 00:44:48,348
She'll be taking Mr. Steuben's desk.

638
00:44:48,452 --> 00:44:49,851
Nice to meet you.

639
00:44:51,588 --> 00:44:53,488
I don't feel so swell.

640
00:44:53,590 --> 00:44:55,182
I think I should go home.

641
00:44:55,292 --> 00:44:58,159
I have to stop eating off the cart.

642
00:44:58,262 --> 00:45:00,230
If you're trying to find
a way to go out and celebrate,

643
00:45:00,330 --> 00:45:01,797
you should ask your secretary
to cover for you.

644
00:45:01,899 --> 00:45:03,127
Very funny.

645
00:45:04,568 --> 00:45:06,263
Happy Thanksgiving.

646
00:45:06,370 --> 00:45:07,359
You, too, Joan.

647
00:45:07,471 --> 00:45:09,735
David and I had a deal.

648
00:45:09,840 --> 00:45:11,432
No meetings in here, okay?

649
00:45:11,541 --> 00:45:12,599
And no music.

650
00:45:27,257 --> 00:45:28,884
What can we do for you today?

651
00:45:28,992 --> 00:45:31,654
My stomach hurts really bad.

652
00:45:31,762 --> 00:45:34,458
I think I had a bad sandwich.

653
00:45:34,564 --> 00:45:36,429
Let's take a look.

654
00:45:44,841 --> 00:45:46,308
Oh, my God.

655
00:45:46,410 --> 00:45:50,847
Honey, you didn't mention
that you were expecting.

656
00:45:50,948 --> 00:45:52,643
What?

657
00:45:52,749 --> 00:45:54,478
You're going to be a mother.

658
00:45:58,255 --> 00:45:59,517
That's impossible.

659
00:45:59,623 --> 00:46:03,150
You want us to call your husband
or your boyfriend?

660
00:46:05,595 --> 00:46:06,789
I don't understand.

661
00:46:06,897 --> 00:46:08,330
Stop talking.

662
00:46:11,668 --> 00:46:14,296
Now listen, we're going
to get you up to Maternity.

663
00:46:14,404 --> 00:46:17,805
No. No, that's not possible.

664
00:46:24,915 --> 00:46:26,314
Do you feel that?

665
00:46:39,830 --> 00:46:40,888
My God!

666
00:46:40,998 --> 00:46:42,295
We need a wheelchair.

667
00:46:42,399 --> 00:46:43,798
It hurts!

668
00:46:43,900 --> 00:46:45,765
It's going to be okay, all right?

669
00:46:45,869 --> 00:46:47,427
We just want you to calm down.

670
00:46:47,537 --> 00:46:48,435
You don't understand.

671
00:46:48,538 --> 00:46:50,369
We need a wheelchair!

672
00:46:53,677 --> 00:46:56,510
Call Dr. Wilson in Psychiatry.

673
00:47:06,590 --> 00:47:08,581
Oh.

674
00:47:08,692 --> 00:47:10,353
Hello, darling.

675
00:47:15,565 --> 00:47:17,760
Oh, were they having
a party at the office?

676
00:47:17,868 --> 00:47:18,892
Yes.

677
00:47:20,537 --> 00:47:22,437
I think I should...

678
00:47:22,539 --> 00:47:23,972
lie down.

679
00:47:24,074 --> 00:47:26,634
That's a good idea.

680
00:47:26,743 --> 00:47:28,802
Sure. Rest up.

681
00:47:28,912 --> 00:47:31,005
But make sure you're awake later.

682
00:47:31,114 --> 00:47:32,741
Daddy!

683
00:47:58,075 --> 00:48:00,976
Would you like to try to feed him?

684
00:48:04,381 --> 00:48:06,849
Don't you want
to hold him, sweetheart?

685
00:48:55,699 --> 00:48:57,291
Hello?

686
00:48:57,400 --> 00:48:59,231
Don?

687
00:49:06,576 --> 00:49:08,009
What are you doing here?

688
00:49:08,111 --> 00:49:10,477
Daddy! Are you coming with us?

689
00:49:10,580 --> 00:49:13,981
No, he isn't. Daddy has to work.

690
00:49:14,084 --> 00:49:15,949
But you can drive us
to the station.

691
00:49:16,052 --> 00:49:17,417
I haven't called the taxi yet.

692
00:49:17,521 --> 00:49:18,988
I'm coming with you.

693
00:49:20,957 --> 00:49:23,255
Really?

694
00:49:23,360 --> 00:49:25,225
You are?

695
00:49:25,328 --> 00:49:26,852
I'll pack the car.

696
00:49:26,963 --> 00:49:28,555
We'll be there before midnight.

697
00:49:35,972 --> 00:49:36,961
Daddy's coming with you.

698
00:49:37,073 --> 00:49:37,971
- Daddy!
- Daddy!

699
00:49:40,544 --> 00:49:42,569
Oh, my goodness.

700
00:49:51,054 --> 00:49:52,146
Hello?

701
00:49:55,659 --> 00:49:56,887
Hello.

